1
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:14,433
<i>I think it's time for us
to move on from your mom.</i>

2
00:00:14,567 --> 00:00:19,933
<i>Let's focus on getting
our family together.</i>

3
00:00:20,067 --> 00:00:21,267
<i> I have the proof!</i>

4
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:23,833
<i>This proves that Jade and Logan
are conspiring against you.</i>

5
00:00:23,967 --> 00:00:25,133
<i>- Come with me.
- Logan!</i>

6
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:26,000
<i>- Come with me.
- What are you doing?</i>

7
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:28,667
<i> You escaped again?</i>

8
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:32,200
<i>I'll make sure
that you rot in jail!</i>

9
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:33,667
<i> Remember that!</i>

10
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:37,000
<i>- What warehouse?
- I'm here at district...</i>

11
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:39,633
<i>- Hello!
- I lost her again!</i>

12
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:27,733
Zayn?

13
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:43,700
You...

14
00:01:43,833 --> 00:01:44,867
you look...

15
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,233
Wow!

16
00:01:47,367 --> 00:01:48,433
You're beautiful!

17
00:01:51,633 --> 00:01:53,133
Wait a minute...

18
00:01:53,267 --> 00:01:55,400
Where's everybody?

19
00:01:55,533 --> 00:01:56,867
They all left in a hurry.

20
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,433
They said your Aunt Jade
is missing.

21
00:01:58,567 --> 00:02:01,400
What? Where could she be?

22
00:02:07,033 --> 00:02:08,233
Excuse me.

23
00:02:10,267 --> 00:02:11,733
Hello, Uncle Wiro?

24
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,167
What?

25
00:02:17,133 --> 00:02:18,200
Okay.

26
00:02:19,933 --> 00:02:21,433
Mooks, what's the matter?

27
00:02:28,633 --> 00:02:30,400
Dad, come on, pick up the phone!

28
00:02:32,433 --> 00:02:33,533
What's going on, Mooks?

29
00:02:36,033 --> 00:02:36,967
It's grandmother.

30
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:38,700
- She's in danger!
- What?

31
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:40,567
Come on, let's go.

32
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:42,400
Hurry!

33
00:02:42,533 --> 00:02:45,100
You let this old hag escape?

34
00:02:45,233 --> 00:02:48,567
I'm sorry, Ma'am, I dozed off.

35
00:02:48,733 --> 00:02:50,667
That's not an excuse.

36
00:02:56,233 --> 00:02:57,867
And you, old hag.

37
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:01,133
Today is my wedding day.

38
00:03:02,233 --> 00:03:03,567
What are you planning to do?

39
00:03:04,633 --> 00:03:06,100
Are you planning
to ruin my wedding?

40
00:03:07,533 --> 00:03:10,067
Damn you!

41
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:11,867
You're a monster.

42
00:03:15,467 --> 00:03:16,933
Zayn, I think...

43
00:03:17,067 --> 00:03:18,200
I think my gut instinct
is correct.

44
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:20,467
Mommy Jade did something
to grandmother.

45
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,200
I hope we catch up to them.

46
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:24,300
Is this the place?

47
00:03:30,833 --> 00:03:31,633
Ma'am!

48
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:34,833
Ma'am Mookie!

49
00:03:34,967 --> 00:03:36,267
Is that you?

50
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:39,233
You know who I am?

51
00:03:39,367 --> 00:03:40,733
Yes, I do.

52
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:43,067
I was assigned to work
at Artemis Pharmacy.

53
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:44,133
I used to see you there

54
00:03:44,267 --> 00:03:46,167
whenever Ma'am Olive
brings you along.

55
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:48,833
Wait, why are you here?

56
00:03:48,967 --> 00:03:51,933
Isn't it Miss Jade's
wedding today?

57
00:03:52,067 --> 00:03:54,733
My grandmother called me
and told me she was here.

58
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:56,333
So I'm here to pick her up.

59
00:03:56,467 --> 00:03:57,433
What?

60
00:03:57,567 --> 00:04:01,000
No one comes here
other than the employees.

61
00:04:01,133 --> 00:04:03,267
But she told me that she's here.

62
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,167
She said
she's in this warehouse.

63
00:04:05,300 --> 00:04:07,767
Boss, can we check inside?

64
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:09,100
Sure, you can.

65
00:04:09,233 --> 00:04:10,767
I'll go with you.

66
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:15,500
But are you sure this is the
warehouse she's talking about?

67
00:04:15,633 --> 00:04:17,900
So you mean
Artemis has another warehouse?

68
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:19,967
Yes.

69
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:22,533
We have the old warehouse.
It's in San Nicolas.

70
00:04:23,733 --> 00:04:25,333
But it's been abandoned.

71
00:04:25,467 --> 00:04:27,267
And...

72
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,433
Ma'am!

73
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,867
You're despicable!

74
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:35,933
I can't believe
that I longed for you before.

75
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:37,467
I looked for you,

76
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:43,433
only to find a monster!

77
00:04:43,567 --> 00:04:47,467
I wish my first born
were not twins.

78
00:04:47,600 --> 00:04:49,667
I wish I only had Jade.

79
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:51,033
I wish I only had her.

80
00:04:51,167 --> 00:04:54,600
I wish I hadn't given birth
to you.

81
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:59,533
I wish you hadn't formed
into a baby

82
00:04:59,667 --> 00:05:02,600
when I was pregnant
with you and Jade.

83
00:05:02,767 --> 00:05:07,667
I regret giving birth to you!

84
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:13,267
You unimaginable witch!

85
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,567
Ma'am, that's enough!

86
00:05:15,633 --> 00:05:16,800
It really is enough!

87
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:20,867
This old hag
needs to stop pestering me!

88
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:23,533
Dig a hole in the backyard!

89
00:05:23,667 --> 00:05:25,500
Bury this old hag!

90
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:29,400
She's loose tongued!

91
00:05:38,033 --> 00:05:39,567
Move!

92
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:40,700
Yes, Ma'am.

93
00:05:57,533 --> 00:06:00,533
Zayn, I still can't contact
my dad.

94
00:06:00,667 --> 00:06:02,900
Just keep trying.

95
00:06:03,033 --> 00:06:05,767
He's still not picking up!

96
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:09,667
Are we getting close
to San Nicolas?

97
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:10,767
We're almost there.

98
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:23,233
Please...

99
00:06:24,567 --> 00:06:26,633
don't do this to Ma'am Ligaya.

100
00:06:28,133 --> 00:06:30,867
I will keep an eye on her.

101
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:34,100
Will you shut up, Caloy?

102
00:06:34,233 --> 00:06:37,233
Please, don't do this to me,
my child.

103
00:06:37,367 --> 00:06:39,400
I'm begging you, please.

104
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,533
Your child?

105
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:45,067
Oh, please don't call me that!

106
00:06:46,033 --> 00:06:48,500
You don't deserve
to be my mother.

107
00:06:56,967 --> 00:06:59,200
I wasn't talking to you.

108
00:07:01,067 --> 00:07:02,933
I'm talking to Caloy.

109
00:07:03,967 --> 00:07:05,633
He's nothing like you.

110
00:07:05,767 --> 00:07:07,200
Unlike you, he has a heart.

111
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:10,400
He's just forced to do
whatever you ask him to do,

112
00:07:10,533 --> 00:07:12,067
you demon!

113
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:17,467
You're a devil!

114
00:07:18,667 --> 00:07:22,733
Remember this, I will never
call you my child.

115
00:07:22,867 --> 00:07:26,167
Because you don't deserve
to be my child.

116
00:07:26,300 --> 00:07:29,067
Or to be any mother's child.

117
00:07:30,133 --> 00:07:31,233
No.

118
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,733
What did you say?

119
00:07:51,867 --> 00:07:54,067
Bury her, Caloy!

120
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,933
No, Ma'am, I don't think I can.

121
00:07:58,067 --> 00:07:59,667
Oh, please!

122
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,933
Are you feeling guilty now?

123
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:06,433
Do you want me
to send you back to jail?

124
00:08:06,567 --> 00:08:08,600
You're wanted by the police,
right?

125
00:08:08,733 --> 00:08:12,333
I can send you back to jail
and let you rot there!

126
00:08:12,467 --> 00:08:14,800
Let's see what will happen
to your mom

127
00:08:14,933 --> 00:08:16,400
who's in the hospital,

128
00:08:16,533 --> 00:08:18,967
now that no one will pay
the bills?

129
00:08:20,633 --> 00:08:22,100
You're despicable.

130
00:08:22,267 --> 00:08:24,267
- Oh, shut up!
- She's your own mother.

131
00:08:25,433 --> 00:08:26,367
Oh, please,

132
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:28,733
spare me the drama.

133
00:08:28,867 --> 00:08:30,767
Just finish your job.

134
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:32,400
First thing in the morning,

135
00:08:32,533 --> 00:08:36,133
I will transfer one million
into your bank account.

136
00:08:36,267 --> 00:08:37,333
Does that sound good?

137
00:08:38,367 --> 00:08:39,367
Go!

138
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,000
I need to go.

139
00:08:47,367 --> 00:08:48,800
Please forgive me, Miss Ligaya.

140
00:08:49,967 --> 00:08:51,000
<i> Hello, Astrid?</i>

141
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:54,700
I'm going straight to the venue.

142
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,367
I'll retouch my makeup there.

143
00:08:58,167 --> 00:08:59,533
You're already there?

144
00:08:59,667 --> 00:09:00,900
Perfect.

145
00:09:01,033 --> 00:09:02,500
I'm on my way.

146
00:09:06,933 --> 00:09:09,100
Finish your job, Caloy.

147
00:09:29,967 --> 00:09:30,933
You monster!

148
00:09:32,633 --> 00:09:33,767
Stop the car!

149
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:34,900
No.

150
00:09:35,033 --> 00:09:36,033
I said, stop the car!

151
00:09:36,167 --> 00:09:37,867
- Knock it off!
- Stop the car! Now!

152
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,667
No matter what you do,
I will never let you go!

153
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:41,533
You bastard!
Logan, stop the car!

154
00:09:41,667 --> 00:09:42,833
I said, no!

155
00:09:44,533 --> 00:09:45,867
What are you doing?

156
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:46,967
What are you doing?

157
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,100
Stop!

158
00:09:49,233 --> 00:09:50,500
Knock it off!

159
00:09:53,900 --> 00:09:54,600
Emma!

160
00:10:00,267 --> 00:10:02,767
- Sir! Sir, please help me.
- What's going on?

161
00:10:02,933 --> 00:10:04,367
Come here!

162
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:05,367
Sir, wait!

163
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:08,100
- What's going on?
- What's your problem?

164
00:10:08,233 --> 00:10:10,400
What's the matter with you?

165
00:10:10,533 --> 00:10:11,267
Sir, Sir!

166
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:13,567
Sir.

167
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:15,633
Go, Ma'am, run!

168
00:10:15,767 --> 00:10:16,767
Stop it! Emma!

169
00:10:26,267 --> 00:10:27,633
You meddler!

170
00:10:29,333 --> 00:10:32,433
Come here, who told you
to get involved?

171
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:37,367
Don't get involved!

172
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:41,367
Emma!

173
00:10:45,533 --> 00:10:46,667
<i> Mooks, look!</i>

174
00:10:49,533 --> 00:10:51,267
There are footsteps!

175
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:03,700
Hey, Bro.

176
00:11:03,833 --> 00:11:04,700
Congrats.

177
00:11:04,833 --> 00:11:06,033
Thank you.

178
00:11:06,167 --> 00:11:06,967
This is Nika.

179
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,200
- Hi, Nika.
- Congrats.

180
00:11:08,367 --> 00:11:09,267
Thank you.

181
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:10,600
Where's your bride?

182
00:11:10,733 --> 00:11:12,533
How come the bridal car
isn't here yet?

183
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:15,433
She's not here yet.

184
00:11:15,567 --> 00:11:18,433
Why don't you look happy, Bro?

185
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:25,733
You look like a man who's forced
to get married at gunpoint.

186
00:11:26,933 --> 00:11:27,967
Is that so?

187
00:11:29,367 --> 00:11:30,433
That's not true.

188
00:11:30,567 --> 00:11:32,300
You guys should go inside.

189
00:11:32,433 --> 00:11:33,967
- I'll see you there.
- Okay, congrats again.

190
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:35,600
Thank you.

191
00:11:43,067 --> 00:11:44,900
<i> Am I doing the right thing?</i>

192
00:11:48,767 --> 00:11:51,400
- Let's go, let's get ready.
- Miss Jade is here.

193
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:54,633
Let's go. Mitch! Please hurry,
double time on makeup.

194
00:11:54,767 --> 00:11:56,000
Make sure she looks fresh.

195
00:11:56,133 --> 00:11:59,133
- Yes, Ma'am.
- I'll just call Miss Astrid.

196
00:11:59,267 --> 00:12:01,000
No need.
You don't need to call her.

197
00:12:01,133 --> 00:12:02,833
Is Mookie here now?

198
00:12:02,967 --> 00:12:05,300
- I'm going to check outside.
- Okay, come on.

199
00:12:05,433 --> 00:12:06,300
Fix me up.

200
00:12:09,433 --> 00:12:10,367
Grandmother?

201
00:12:12,233 --> 00:12:13,067
Grandmother!

202
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,400
Mrs. Ligaya!

203
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:18,433
- Mrs. Ligaya.
- Grandmother?

204
00:12:18,567 --> 00:12:19,767
Grandmother, we're here!

205
00:12:19,900 --> 00:12:21,667
Grandmother, where are you?

206
00:12:23,433 --> 00:12:25,200
- Mrs. Ligaya!
- Grandmother!

207
00:12:29,133 --> 00:12:31,233
- Grandmother!
- Mrs. Ligaya!

208
00:12:31,367 --> 00:12:33,900
Grandmother, where are you?

209
00:12:34,033 --> 00:12:36,267
- Mrs. Ligaya?
- Grandmother?

210
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:40,067
Zayn, Zayn!

211
00:12:50,267 --> 00:12:51,367
- Zayn.
- Mooks.

212
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:52,267
Grandmother?

213
00:12:53,967 --> 00:12:55,000
Grandmother?

214
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:57,400
Grandmother?

215
00:12:57,533 --> 00:12:58,467
Grandmother!

216
00:12:59,933 --> 00:13:01,467
- Mooks!
- Grandmother!

217
00:13:05,667 --> 00:13:07,433
- Grandmother!
- Mrs.Ligaya!

218
00:13:07,567 --> 00:13:08,867
Grandmother!

219
00:13:11,533 --> 00:13:12,500
Sir!

220
00:13:14,167 --> 00:13:17,800
Miss Jade is here.
She's getting dressed.

221
00:13:17,933 --> 00:13:21,333
I couldn't contact my daughter.

222
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:23,133
There's no signal in here.

223
00:13:23,267 --> 00:13:25,900
Excuse me,
I'm going to assist Miss Jade.

224
00:13:26,033 --> 00:13:27,833
- Okay, go ahead.
- Okay.

225
00:13:35,667 --> 00:13:36,967
Miss Jade.

226
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:38,433
Miss Jade,
I'm sorry to interrupt.

227
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:39,900
Mr. Danilo's getting worried.

228
00:13:40,033 --> 00:13:41,667
He couldn't get hold
of Miss Mookie.

229
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:43,567
The program is about to start.

230
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:45,633
- What?
- Yes.

231
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:50,600
- Love!
- Hi, Sir!

232
00:13:50,733 --> 00:13:51,500
What are you doing here?

233
00:13:51,633 --> 00:13:52,833
You're not supposed
to see me yet.

234
00:13:52,967 --> 00:13:54,033
Is that so? I'm sorry.

235
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:56,533
It's just that
I couldn't get hold of Mookie.

236
00:13:56,667 --> 00:13:59,800
I've been trying to call her.
But she's not here yet.

237
00:14:02,067 --> 00:14:02,900
Why?

238
00:14:03,033 --> 00:14:04,433
Where could she be?

239
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:10,033
Grandmother?

240
00:14:16,433 --> 00:14:18,933
No! Zayn.

241
00:14:19,067 --> 00:14:22,267
Grandmother!

242
00:14:23,233 --> 00:14:26,300
Zayn! Get grandmother out!

243
00:14:26,433 --> 00:14:28,033
Mrs. Ligaya!

244
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:33,000
Get grandmother out!

245
00:14:34,567 --> 00:14:35,900
Zayn, hurry up!

246
00:14:36,033 --> 00:14:38,767
My grandmother might not make it
to the hospital!

247
00:14:38,900 --> 00:14:40,433
Drive faster!

248
00:14:40,567 --> 00:14:42,233
Yes, I will, Mooks.

249
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:52,000
- Okay, I will call her.
- Okay.

250
00:15:06,067 --> 00:15:07,533
She's not picking up.

251
00:15:10,633 --> 00:15:12,800
You know what? Let's start
with the wedding anyway.

252
00:15:12,933 --> 00:15:15,733
Mookie will be here.
I'm sure she's on her way here.

253
00:15:16,133 --> 00:15:19,033
Wait a minute. We'll still push
through with the wedding

254
00:15:19,167 --> 00:15:20,900
even without Mookie?

255
00:15:21,033 --> 00:15:22,567
Of course, Love.

256
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:23,967
The pastor
has other appointments.

257
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:28,200
And we can't make our guests
wait too long.

258
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:31,767
Love, I'm sure Mookie
will understand.

259
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:34,067
She'll be here soon.

260
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:35,733
It's all going to be okay.

261
00:15:35,900 --> 00:15:37,300
All right?

262
00:15:37,433 --> 00:15:38,400
But...

263
00:15:39,867 --> 00:15:40,767
Ma'am,

264
00:15:40,900 --> 00:15:43,567
- she's your Maid of Honor.
- That's right.

265
00:15:43,700 --> 00:15:45,167
Well, then...

266
00:15:45,300 --> 00:15:47,200
you can be my Maid of Honor.

267
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:48,500
- Me?
- Yes.

268
00:15:48,633 --> 00:15:49,933
Come on, let's go.

269
00:15:50,067 --> 00:15:51,200
- Look at the time.
- Ma'am, why me?

270
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:52,933
Let's not make our guests wait.

271
00:15:53,067 --> 00:15:54,233
Let's start in a bit.

272
00:15:54,367 --> 00:15:56,100
I'll be ready in a few seconds.

273
00:15:57,067 --> 00:15:59,800
Zayn!

274
00:15:59,933 --> 00:16:02,467
Hurry!

275
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,800
Grandmother?

276
00:16:04,933 --> 00:16:06,733
Grandmother!

277
00:16:06,867 --> 00:16:08,467
Grandmother.

278
00:16:08,633 --> 00:16:11,733
- Mookie? My dear!
- Grandmother!

279
00:16:11,867 --> 00:16:12,833
Mookie!

280
00:16:14,267 --> 00:16:17,733
Did Mommy Jade do this to you?

281
00:16:19,933 --> 00:16:22,033
Not Jade.

282
00:16:22,167 --> 00:16:23,300
It's Olive.

283
00:16:25,067 --> 00:16:26,233
It's...

284
00:16:26,367 --> 00:16:28,467
- It's Olive.
- Mommy did this?

285
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:31,167
Olive did this to me!

286
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:33,367
How is that possible?

287
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:41,000
Where are we going?

288
00:16:41,133 --> 00:16:42,233
We're bringing you
to the hospital, Grandmother.

289
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:44,067
You have to get checked.

290
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:45,033
No.

291
00:16:45,167 --> 00:16:46,333
No...

292
00:16:46,467 --> 00:16:48,000
We have to go straight
to the wedding.

293
00:16:48,133 --> 00:16:51,933
- Let's go to the wedding.
- But, Grandmother.

294
00:16:52,067 --> 00:16:54,867
You have to listen to me, Dear.

295
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,767
We need to go to the wedding
this instant.

296
00:16:57,900 --> 00:16:59,733
You have to trust me on this.

297
00:16:59,867 --> 00:17:02,067
We have to call the police.

298
00:17:05,033 --> 00:17:06,333
Okay, Grandmother.

299
00:17:06,467 --> 00:17:09,300
Zayn, let's head to the wedding
right now.

300
00:17:09,433 --> 00:17:10,533
Okay, Mooks.

301
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:34,633
<i> Good day, everyone.</i>

302
00:18:34,767 --> 00:18:35,867
We're all gathered here today

303
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:39,700
to witness Danilo
and Jade's nuptials.

304
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:43,000
If anyone objects
to this marriage,

305
00:18:44,033 --> 00:18:45,433
speak now,

306
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:51,833
or forever hold your peace.

307
00:18:51,967 --> 00:18:53,467
Let's begin.

308
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:58,767
Stop the wedding!

309
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:02,600
Emma?

310
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:05,500
What the hell!

311
00:19:06,567 --> 00:19:09,200
What are you doing here?
You're pestering us again!

312
00:19:09,333 --> 00:19:11,433
Can you leave us alone?

313
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:14,167
Danilo...

314
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:15,700
didn't you ask for proof

315
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:18,400
that Jade and Logan
conspired against me?

316
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:21,433
I have it here.

317
00:19:21,567 --> 00:19:23,200
You have to see this.

318
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:25,467
Please, leave us alone!

319
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:27,433
Get her out of here!

320
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:28,833
Shut up!

321
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,100
- You should shut up!
- Dan, you have to listen to me.

322
00:19:31,233 --> 00:19:32,500
Please...

323
00:19:32,633 --> 00:19:33,667
Love!

324
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:35,567
Why did you take that? Wait!

325
00:19:35,700 --> 00:19:37,933
Dan!

326
00:19:38,067 --> 00:19:39,367
Bro,

327
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:41,100
can you play this for me?

328
00:19:41,233 --> 00:19:44,867
<i>Danilo, please don't listen
to her!</i>

329
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:47,667
She's lying and is trying
to ruin me!

330
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:49,133
Love, what's going on with you?

331
00:19:49,267 --> 00:19:52,567
Why are you listening
to that woman?

332
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:54,233
Sir, play it, please.

333
00:19:54,367 --> 00:19:56,000
Love, please.

334
00:20:25,167 --> 00:20:26,833
What's the meaning of this,
Jade?

335
00:20:29,300 --> 00:20:32,067
You clearly saw
that Jade gave Logan something.

336
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:34,833
And that's what Logan put
in my drink.

337
00:20:38,100 --> 00:20:40,000
Love, please let me explain.

338
00:20:41,933 --> 00:20:43,500
No, no, no, no, no, no.

339
00:20:43,633 --> 00:20:46,533
I didn't conspire with Jade.

340
00:20:48,567 --> 00:20:49,500
Emma,

341
00:20:49,633 --> 00:20:50,900
how could you?

342
00:20:52,033 --> 00:20:53,433
Logan!

343
00:21:00,233 --> 00:21:04,033
Wait, I'll try to call dad.

344
00:21:04,967 --> 00:21:06,400
Wait, Grandmother.

345
00:21:09,067 --> 00:21:10,567
Where's my phone?

346
00:21:34,767 --> 00:21:36,467
Dad, please!

347
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:43,800
He's not picking up!

348
00:21:43,967 --> 00:21:46,000
Maybe the wedding ceremony
has started.

349
00:21:46,133 --> 00:21:47,400
No!

350
00:21:47,533 --> 00:21:49,867
No, they can't get married!
The wedding can't go on!

351
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:52,600
That can't happen!
The wedding can't go on!

352
00:21:52,733 --> 00:21:54,367
- We need to hurry!
- Zayn, hurry up!

353
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:55,967
Drive faster,
we might not make it on time!

354
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:59,133
Buckle up!
Mooks, hold on to Mrs. Ligaya.

355
00:22:05,333 --> 00:22:06,933
Danilo,

356
00:22:07,067 --> 00:22:09,933
that CCTV footage
that you've watched...

357
00:22:10,067 --> 00:22:12,033
It's old.

358
00:22:12,167 --> 00:22:14,200
I haven't even met Emma
at that time.

359
00:22:15,367 --> 00:22:17,733
And what Jade gave me
at that time...

360
00:22:17,867 --> 00:22:19,300
that's not drugs...

361
00:22:19,433 --> 00:22:20,767
that's not medicine...

362
00:22:20,900 --> 00:22:22,267
that was a calling card...

363
00:22:23,333 --> 00:22:25,067
of Satoshi Sato.

364
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:27,400
I've been looking for him.

365
00:22:27,533 --> 00:22:30,800
Thank you, Jade,
I got hold of him.

366
00:22:30,933 --> 00:22:32,100
You're a liar!

367
00:22:32,233 --> 00:22:33,900
Liar!

368
00:22:34,033 --> 00:22:35,200
I'm just telling the truth.

369
00:22:36,833 --> 00:22:37,633
So, Danilo,

370
00:22:38,667 --> 00:22:40,267
the footage you saw,

371
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:42,233
whether you believe me or not,

372
00:22:42,367 --> 00:22:43,767
Emma just made it up.

373
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:46,633
I don't know how she did it,
but...

374
00:22:46,767 --> 00:22:48,733
don't worry, after this wedding,

375
00:22:48,900 --> 00:22:50,400
I'll show you the whole footage.

376
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:54,433
You don't have another video!
Stop making up stories!

377
00:22:54,567 --> 00:22:57,100
I'm not making up stories.

378
00:22:57,233 --> 00:22:59,167
You are.

379
00:22:59,300 --> 00:23:00,800
You hate Jade, don't you?

380
00:23:02,267 --> 00:23:04,567
So now that we know the truth.

381
00:23:04,700 --> 00:23:06,167
Emma, please...

382
00:23:06,300 --> 00:23:07,767
leave now.

383
00:23:07,900 --> 00:23:09,733
Dan, you have to believe me...

384
00:23:09,867 --> 00:23:12,600
- Please, leave!
- Dan, I'm telling the truth!

385
00:23:12,733 --> 00:23:14,733
Leave us alone!

386
00:23:14,867 --> 00:23:16,500
What the heck!

387
00:23:16,633 --> 00:23:18,633
Get this woman out!

388
00:23:25,900 --> 00:23:28,867
This is not acceptable, Emma!

389
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:32,067
You have to believe me, Dan.
She's a liar!

390
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:33,700
Get out of my wedding!

391
00:23:33,833 --> 00:23:35,800
Logan, can you please...

392
00:23:35,933 --> 00:23:37,533
take this woman out?

393
00:23:37,667 --> 00:23:41,200
Hurry up, we might not
make it on time.

394
00:23:41,333 --> 00:23:42,567
Let's continue on.

395
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:45,100
Stop this nonsense!

396
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:49,500
- Mom?
- Auntie Ligaya.

397
00:23:50,667 --> 00:23:52,833
The wedding's not going
to happen!

398
00:23:58,933 --> 00:24:01,467
That woman is Satan's offspring!

399
00:24:03,367 --> 00:24:04,800
She's a con artist!

400
00:24:04,933 --> 00:24:05,933
A liar!

401
00:24:06,067 --> 00:24:07,400
A demon!

402
00:24:07,533 --> 00:24:09,933
She buried me alive!

403
00:24:12,467 --> 00:24:13,400
Danilo!

404
00:24:14,467 --> 00:24:18,333
That woman you're about
to marry is a murderer!

405
00:24:18,467 --> 00:24:20,533
That's not Jade!

406
00:24:20,667 --> 00:24:22,533
Jade is dead!

407
00:24:22,667 --> 00:24:25,167
That woman killed her!

408
00:24:25,300 --> 00:24:27,167
She's pretending to be Jade!

409
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:30,400
The truth is, she's Olive!

410
00:24:30,567 --> 00:24:32,433
You're Olive!

411
00:24:32,567 --> 00:24:36,133
Tell them the truth, Olive!

412
00:24:57,367 --> 00:24:58,667
Come with me.

413
00:24:58,800 --> 00:25:00,133
You're coming with me!

414
00:25:00,267 --> 00:25:02,100
I'm not coming with you!

415
00:25:02,267 --> 00:25:04,767
No, Mookie! You're mine!

416
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:07,567
You need to go to the hospital.

417
00:25:07,700 --> 00:25:09,700
I don't need to go
to the hospital.

418
00:25:09,833 --> 00:25:11,933
I need to see Emma.

419
00:25:12,067 --> 00:25:13,267
I need to see Mookie.

420
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:16,567
I need to make sure
that my family is safe.

421
00:25:16,700 --> 00:25:19,000
Mom, help me! Mom!

422
00:25:19,133 --> 00:25:21,700
I will do everything for Mookie!
